module
import %supershow%/src/supershow.vfx
import %supershow%/3d/model.vfx
import %supershow%/3d/cube.vfx
public

\ Minimal 3D demo: one colored cube spinning about its Y axis.
\ Validates the ported 3dpack pipeline (projection, vertex buffer, modelview,
\ indexed/non-indexed draw). Camera is the identity transform; the cube sits
\ in front of it. If it isn't visible, tune `pos` z, `scl`, or `fov`.

%model object thecube

\ Access v3d props via `-> name` (not `>name`): the >pos accessor would collide
\ with VFX's console `>pos` primitive.
: setup ( - )
    cube-mesh thecube /model        \ set mesh (and unit scale)
    0 0 -6 thecube -> pos s>v3       \ 6 units in front of the camera
    1 1 1  thecube -> scl s>v3 ;     \ cube spans -1..+1 -- bump this to enlarge

: ~render ( - )
    cls                             \ clear color buffer (backdrop, default black)
    3d                              \ set perspective projection + clear depth
    1. thecube -> pan +!            \ spin 1 degree/frame about Y
    thecube draw-model ;

: main ( - )
    setup
    show> ~render ;

main
